-- Korean Regulator Plans Routine Review of Citigroup Unit
-- B y   S e o n j i n   C h a
-- 2012-01-11T08:27:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/korea-regulator-plans-regular-probe-on-citi-s-korea-unit-in-2012.html
South Korea ’s Financial Supervisory
Service is planning a regular inspection of  Citigroup Inc. (C) ’s
local banking unit this year, the regulator said in an e-mailed
statement today.  James Griffiths, a Hong Kong-based spokesman for Citigroup,
declined to comment on the plan to review Citibank Korea Inc.  Citibank Korea is the Asian nation’s seventh-largest lender
by assets as of March 2011, according to FSS data.  To contact the reporter on this story:
